-- Bartolo Colon Agrees to One-Year Contract With Oakland Athletics
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-01-24T20:40:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/bartolo-colon-agrees-to-one-year-contract-with-oakland-athletics.html
The  Oakland Athletics  signed free-
agent pitcher  Bartolo Colon  to a one-year contract, the Major
League Baseball team said.  Colon, 38, went 8-10 with a 4.00 earned-run average for the
 New York  Yankees last season.  The righthander has a record of 161-113 during a 14-year
career with  Cleveland ,  Montreal , Anaheim/ Los Angeles , the
 Chicago White Sox ,  Boston  and New York.  He won the 2005 American League Cy Young award when he went
21-8 for the Angels.  Financial terms weren't disclosed.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  